Comparison of Linked Lists:

Procedure || Linear Singly Linked List | Circular Singly LL | Linear Doubly LL | Circular Doubly LL
----------++---------------------------+--------------------+------------------+--------------------
Traversal || Unidirectional            | Unidirectional	    | Bidirectional    | Bidirectional and
	      ||                           | and circular       |                  | circular 
----------++---------------------------+--------------------+------------------+--------------------
Insert    || O(n)                      | O(n)               | O(n)             | O(n)                    Note: becasue of O(n), only first (and last for circular) pos is O(n);
----------++---------------------------+--------------------+------------------+--------------------
Deletion  || Same as Insertion         | >                  | >                | > 
----------++---------------------------+--------------------+------------------+--------------------
Space     || O(n)                      | O(n)               | O(2n)            | O(2n)                  Note: 2n = n in big o notation but its just to illustrate the doubly links.
----------++---------------------------+--------------------+------------------+--------------------


LL: use for queues and times where you never need to go back, can use linear/circular

DCLL: same as linear LL so is always a good choice, but uses more memory than singly-linked list




